    {
      "id": "dictionary-runtime-merge",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Runtime Merge Behavior",
      "position": {
        "x": 753.1490924526647,
        "y": 382.57461697345457
      },
      "width": 685.6179272613672,
      "height": 227.8103779105477,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "markdown": "## Runtime Merge (Transition Behavior)\n\n- Runtime may still build a compatibility dictionary projection\n- Imported dictionary entries are fallback data only\n- Bridge-derived registry state should resolve before dictionary fallback\n- **No persistence** back to the graph is required for derived projections\n- Unknown unresolved custom node types should fail visibly through shared error surfaces instead of causing new dictionary infrastructure to be invented\n- Version mismatches may warn, but dictionary presence alone should not imply authority\n\nThis preserves compatibility while dictionary authority is being demoted.",
